## Detailed Workflow Steps
1. User Authentication
- User signs into React app via Amazon Cognito
- Cognito provides JWT bearer token for authenticated sessions
- Token includes user identity and authorized scopes

2. Request Flow Through Gateway
- React app makes API calls to AgentCore Gateway with JWT token
- Gateway validates token and applies policy-based authorization
- Policy Engine evaluates request against defined policies
- Amazon Bedrock Guardrails screen requests for:
- - Content filtering (violence, hate, sexual content, etc.)
- - Prompt injection attacks
- - Sensitive information (PII, credentials)
- - Custom organizational policies

3. Request/Response Interceptors
- Lambda functions inspect and transform traffic
- Can implement custom business logic, logging, or additional security checks
- Support both buffered and streaming modes

4. AgentCore Runtime Execution
- Gateway routes approved requests to AgentCore Runtime
- Runtime executes in isolated MicroVM environment
- Agent orchestration via Strands Agents or LangGraph
- Access to MCP tools and external APIs through gateway

5. Response Processing
- Runtime generates response through foundation model
- Response flows back through gateway guardrails
- Interceptors can modify or log responses
- Streaming responses delivered to React app in real-time

## Key Security Features
- Multi-layered Security: Authentication, authorization, guardrails, and interceptors
- Session Isolation: Each user session runs in dedicated MicroVM
- Identity Propagation: JWT tokens carry user context throughout system
- Audit Logging: Complete request/response logging via CloudWatch and X-Ray


